---
import ChapterLayout from "../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro";
import BinderHoles from "../components/BinderHoles.astro";
import Backlink from "../components/Backlink.astro";
---

<ChapterLayout title="Preamble" headVoice="publisher">
  <div data-voice="publisher">
    <BinderHoles />
    <Backlink />
    <p>
      In recent months, controversy has sparked across <a
        href="https://severance.wiki/kier_pe">Kier</a
      > and beyond concerning the ethical treatment of severed employees at <a
        href="https://severance.wiki/lumon_industries">Lumon Industries</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p>
      We find these allegations most disturbing, and we take them seriously.
    </p>
    <p>
      We care too much for our <a href="https://severance.wiki/lumon_industries"
        >Lumon</a
      > family members to allow mistreatment to go unmediated. So, rest assured that
      <a href="https://severance.wiki/lumon_industries">Lumon</a> henceforth commits
      to new degrees of transparency that will give &quot;innies&quot; a greater voice
      which can be heard. In tandem, we commit to giving &quot;outies&quot; a more
      clear glimpse into the life and treatment of their counterparts.
    </p>
    <p>This leads us to the purpose of this document.</p>
    <p>
      We begin with a simple question: <strong
        >what is it like to be an &quot;innie&quot;?</strong
      >
    </p>
    <p>We want to show you.</p>
    <p>
      This of course could be shown with photos, videos, the written word, etc.
      - but these second-hand glimpses are much different compared to <strong
        >experiencing it for yourself.</strong
      >
    </p>
    <p>
      You might then ask: how can anyone experience being an &quot;innie&quot;?
      Even our severed employees have no recollection of the experience. The
      answer: after months of research and development, <a
        href="https://severance.wiki/lumon_industries">Lumon</a
      >&#x27;s Public Relations department has come up with delightful solution
      that utilizes the power of play and imagination.
    </p>
    <p>
      Welcome to <a href="/table-of-contents">Severed Story</a> - a light-hearted
      role-playing game system for describing the wonders of &quot;innie&quot; life
      within the walls of <a href="https://severance.wiki/lumon_industries"
        >Lumon</a
      >! In this document you will find rules and regulations to aid you in the
      accurate simulation of the innie experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      So read on loyal customers and prospective employees! We hope the stories
      you live out will open your eyes to the joys of severed life.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <div data-panel-type="note">
      <div>
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
        >
          <path d="M15 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7Z"
          ></path>
          <path d="M14 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><em><strong>Dear reader,</strong></em></p>
        <p>
          <em
            >Within the walls of this document you will find many half truths,
            and many whole lies.</em
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          <em
            >Over the last decade, I have worked closely with a number of real
            life &quot;innies&quot; in an undercover capacity. I know first-hand
            that not all is as it seems within Lumon Industries. While yes,
            there is the potential for a life to be had there, it often turns
            ugly - even torturous.</em
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          <em
            >As you continue reading this &quot;rules document&quot;, please
            look for the notes I&#x27;ve left behind within the pages. I&#x27;ve
            risked my safety to desecrate as many copies of <a
              href="/table-of-contents">Severed Story</a
            > that I could get my hands on. My goal is to essentially augment the
            rules of this so-called &quot;game&quot; so as to reveal what life at
            Lumon is truly like.</em
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>Don&#x27;t be fooled by this propaganda. Look for my notes.</em>
        </p>
        <p><em><strong>Best regards,</strong></em></p>
        <p><em><strong>Concerned Citizen</strong></em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ChapterLayout>
